userinterface.graph

Class GraphResultListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • userinterface.graph.GraphResultListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ResultListener

    public class GraphResultListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements ResultListener
    This class is responsible for mapping output of a ResultsCollection to the input of a GraphModel. Used to be called Displayable Data.

      • GraphResultListener

        public GraphResultListener(Graph graph,
                           Graph.SeriesKey seriesKey,
                           java.lang.String rangeConstant,
                           Values otherValues)
        Creates a new instance of GraphResultListener It presumes that the seriesKey is returned by a call of graph.addSeries(...).
        Parameters:
        graph - The graph to notify when new results are found.
        seriesKey - The key of the series this listener represents.
        rangeConstant - The ranging constant (x-axis value) (required to identify the series from the results).
        otherValues - Values of all other constants of this series (required to identify the series from the results).

    • Method Detail

      • notifyResult

        public void notifyResult(ResultsCollection resultsCollection,
                         Values values,
                         java.lang.Object result)
        Description copied from interface: ResultListener
        This method is called whenever a ResultCollection discovers a new result.
        Specified by:
        notifyResult in interface ResultListener
        Parameters:
        resultsCollection - The ResultsCollection from which this result is a member.
        values - The parameters of the experiment.
        result - The result of the experiment (any of Exception, Integer, Boolean, Double, null). Be aware that valid Double values include NaN, and plus and minus infinity.

      • isInSeries

        private java.lang.Object isInSeries(Values v)
        Looks at the values and sees whether it matches otherValues, apart from one which should match 'rangeConstant'. If so this method returns the value of the rangeConstant (x-axis). If not this returns null.
